reviews.text: the hotel has what has to be one of the best views of Victoria harbour from the pool and the rooms. could sit all day watching the changing view. we ate once in the hotel and the food was outstanding. the rooms are clean and the bed is great. I would recommend the hotel without hesitation

Great short stay in Hong Kong. Close to MTR station which made getting around very easy. Able to visit all the main tourist locations. Great staff behind reception and at breakfast. Concierge staff also always had a friendly and personal approach to service. Comfortable clean room with water supplied every day. Efficient and cost effective transport service to and from airport.

Good hotel, welcoming staff, great location, amazing service 
Rooms are a bit old and small but still has a quality and vibe to them.
Amazing view from the hotel rooms.
Nothing to complain about at all.

Room is pretty standard and not much of a view unless facing the harbour. Recommend upgrading to a harbour facing room which comes with free breakfast. Rooftop is popular and the views are spectacular. Would be a great place to relax when the sun is shining but could be improved with a bar or snacks available

Staff were helpful, particularly in the restaurant. Restaurant food was great with nice choice for evening buffet. Room was small and simple though. Roof pool was freezing and not warm enough to swim (end March). OK stay, but I wouldn't consider it a 4-star
